headline: Corrections & Amplifications
summary: A Business & Finance article on Monday about job-applicant tracking systems incorrectly implied it started after the Sept. 11 terrorist attacks.  Walgreens Boots Alliance reported a net loss of $175 million for its latest quarter.  In some editions Friday, a What’s News item and display text for a Business & Finance article about the drugstore chain incorrectly said losses narrowed.

headline: Shell denies deal talks with BP, Micron reports Q3 beat: Morning Buzz
summary: The major averages were higher near noon, with the S&P 500 continuing its path towards all-time highs reached earlier this year. Meanwhile, the U.S. dollar is under pressure amid the worst first-half performance in 50 years, falling to its lowest since early 2022 amid speculation that President Trump may replace Fed Chair Powell before his term ends and markets pricing in over 60 basis points of rate cuts by year-end.
